// =============================================================================
// core/logic/mod.vr — Stdlib surface for non-classical logic kernels
// =============================================================================
// Layer: Standard Library / Logic
// =============================================================================
//

// Non-classical logic kernels for verification + reasoning over
// modal / linear / temporal / sub-structural propositions:
//

//  * `kripke.vr` — Kripke semantics for modal logic. World-relation
//  models for ◻/◇ modalities, used by the temporal-logic
//  verification path (LTL/CTL backends in
//  `verum_smt::temporal_logic`) and by the epistemic-logic
//  library in `core.math.epistemic`.
//

//  * `linear.vr` — Linear logic primitives (Girard 1987): linear
//  implication ⊸, additive ⊕/&, multiplicative ⊗/⅋, exponentials
//  !/?. The backbone for resource-aware reasoning + the
//  Ludics-design surface in `core.action.ludics`.
//

//  * `separation.vr` — Separation logic primitives (Reynolds 2002 /
//  O'Hearn 2007): heap-shaped propositions, separating conjunction
//  `∗`, points-to `↦`, frame rule. The verification surface for
//  stateful programs (mutating heap, concurrent threads,
//  IO-bearing operations). Mirrors
//  `verum_kernel::separation_logic` so user proof bodies cite
//  the same heap-predicate vocabulary the kernel dispatcher
//  consumes (#161).
//

// Modules expose the abstract syntax + decision procedures;
// the SMT-side encodings live in `verum_smt`. Verum programs
// import these to define propositions over the logic, then use
// `@verify(...)` to discharge them through the matching backend.
// =============================================================================

module core.logic;

public module kripke;
public module linear;
public module separation;
